<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-23T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-23T04:00:00-05:00" n="86" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d86">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/3394: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-23T16:00:00+07:00">August 23,
                                1943—4 p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received August 23—3:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1547. Chungking was raided this morning by some 22 Japanese planes which flew
                        over the city but apparently dropped bombs only in the outskirts near a
                        small arsenal. Some defense by Chinese planes. While Japanese reconnaissance
                        planes have come over occasionally, this is first actual raid since
                        September 1941.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>